Create a small component library (3-5 components) with strict prop typing and component composition patterns.
Components:

Button<T> (generic for onClick event data).

Select<Option> (typed options array and onChange callback).

Form<Schema> (typed field names and validation).
Requirements:

Use React.FC<Props> or function components with explicit types.

Prop validation using discriminated unions (e.g., variant: 'primary' | 'secondary').

Generic components where appropriate.

Strict children typing (children?: React.ReactNode).
Structure:

components/Button/Button.tsx and Button.types.ts.

components/Select/Select.tsx and Select.types.ts.

index.ts for exports.
Tests (using @testing-library/react):

Component rendering.

Event handlers with correct types.

Type errors for invalid props (use @ts-expect-error).